{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c68f6954-4336-4633-945e-9cd1cb562703","content":"Here's how to migrate from `VSTest@3` to `Microsoft.Testing.Platform` in Azure Pipelines:\n\n### 1. Replace `VSTest@3` with `dotnet test`\n\n```yaml\n# Before (VSTest@3)\n- task: VSTest@3\n  inputs:\n    testAssemblies: '**/*.Tests.dll'\n    codeCoverageEnabled: true\n\n# After (Microsoft.Testing.Platform via dotnet test)\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: 'Run tests'\n  inputs:\n    command: 'test'\n    projects: '**/*.Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >-\n      --configuration Release\n      --logger \"trx;LogFileName=results.trx\"\n      --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n      --collect \"Code Coverage;Format=Cobertura\"\n```\n\n### 2. Update your test projects\n\nAdd these to each test `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <!-- Opt into Microsoft.Testing.Platform runner -->\n  <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n  <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n  <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n### 3. Publish TRX results & coverage\n\n```yaml\n- task: PublishTestResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish test results'\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    testResultsFormat: 'VSTest'\n    testResultsFiles: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.trx'\n\n- task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish code coverage'\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/coverage.cobertura.xml'\n```\n\n### Key differences from VSTest@3\n\n| Concern | VSTest@3 | Microsoft.Testing.Platform |\n|---|---|---|\n| Runner | `vstest.console.exe` | In-process (`dotnet test`) |\n| Test discovery | DLL-based globs | Project-based (`*.csproj`) |\n| TRX reports | Built-in | `--logger trx` |\n| Code coverage | `codeCoverageEnabled` | `--collect \"Code Coverage\"` |\n| Publish results | Automatic | Separate `PublishTestResults@2` step |\n\nUse `condition: always()` on the publish steps so results are uploaded even when tests fail.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c12c27ff-4417-47b1-8dca-d940b7634153","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory seems empty. The user is asking a general question about migrating from VSTest@3 to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in Azure DevOps pipelines. Let me provide guidance based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":684,"requestId":"4C14:A0D2E:D2749F:106ADB6:6A01299F"},"id":"8473c974-2f32-46b9-9414-ca0184d1d514","timestamp":"2026-05-11T00:58:20.032Z","parentId":"def5e7c1-af9c-42df-b64a-e7c92e9389c8"}
